A simple thing like owning a pair of school shoes is almost non-existent for some. But Irafaan Abrahams is trying to change that Through his non-profit organisation Lace up for Change. Tanya Nefdt reports. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - A Cape Town school teacher is taking a step in the right direction by helping school kids put their best foot forward. Irafaan Abrahams has managed to raise much-needed funds to provide brand new school shoes to thousands of pupils across the country. During the heart of Covid19 pandemic, Abrahams undertook a major challenge to run 50 half marathons in one year, all to raise funds to purchase shoes for 50 schools across the country. * eNCA's Tanya Nefdt reports.